Conditional statements
In programing there are times that if something is true then you want an operation to occur, but not when a condition is not true. ### Base R These can be done with if and if else statements in base R. These are written if a condition is true then the operation is done. They can be built upon with else if if the first condition is false to do test a second condition. If you want it to be If true and if false do something else then if and else structure can be used.

b = 5 

if (b == 5){
  cat('b = 5 \n') # \n is carriage return to end line when printing
}
## b = 5

if (TRUE){
  c = 6
}else(
  c = 10
)
c 
## [1] 6

